<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="26" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="26">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="26">
Thallus saxicolous, crustose, surface grey, smooth; apothecia lirelline, elongate, subimmersed, single and branched, 1-20 mm long and 0.2-0.3 mm wide, with lateral thalline margin; labia conspicuous; discs open, dark; proper exciple completely carbonized; hymenium clear; 8 ascospores per ascus, brown, ellipsoid, muriform, 4/1-2-locular, 14-16 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
8-9 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="I–">I-</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
